result.execSummary:
The defendant Camara L Hamilton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Camara L Hamilton in court, in custody, with Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris.   Andrea M Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts #1 & 2.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Counts #1 & 2.  Count #3 is dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Harris makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:

2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
 - 1 YEAR OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
 - 1 YEAR OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

TERM OF PROBATION: 2 YEARS   (73 days credit, if revoked)       **transfer allowed to Milwaukee County**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling- - obtain HSED/GED
____No contact with: victim businesses listed in criminal complaint or Pick n Save stores
____Criminal Thinking course
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME: 60 Days,  Non-working hours with standard release conditions - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion


COUNT #2:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:

2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT                  **CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT #1**
 - 1 YEAR OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
 - 1 YEAR OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

TERM OF PROBATION: 2 YEARS   (73 days credit, if revoked)       **transfer allowed to Milwaukee County**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling- - obtain HSED/GED
____No contact with: victim businesses listed in criminal complaint or Pick n Save stores
____Criminal Thinking course
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

COSTS:  $268.00  (to be paid as a condition of probation)

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

NOTE:  Court denies request for expungment
